service registry
A service registry is used in microservice architecture to enable dynamic service discovery
as if now we are hardcoding the url of other microservice whome to talk
Instead of that every microservice will register it self into service registry
In our case job microservice is talking to company microservice like below
restTemplate.getForObject("http://localhost:8081/companies/"+job.getCompanyId(),Company.class);

so Company microservice will register it self to service registry and then job microservice will make service discovery request to service registry 

spring cloud eureka is one of such service registry


for servicereg project we need spring web and spring eureka server two dependencies
now before even starting the application we need to tell springboot to consider this as a eureka server so add @EnableEurekaServer
annotation in ServiceregApplication class a root file

and specify 
eureka.client.register-with-eureka = false
eureka.client.fetch-registry=false

in application.properties

http://localhost:8761/ opens interface for eureka server